  "body": "Hi,\r\n\r\nif I try to run the container in for example openshift I get the error message below because the container has no terminal available. I think I might be smart to not have the entrypoint pointed towards the binary. Try to use something like this as an entry point. Also it could be better to have env vars controlling the params of the binary. \r\n\r\nProposal for new entry point\r\n```\r\n#!/bin/sh\r\nexec $@\r\n```\r\n\r\n```\r\nThis container doesn't have a /bin/sh shell. Try specifying your command in a terminal with:\r\n\r\noc -n default exec beacon-node-5fc7dbf779-qgr62 -ti <command>\r\n```",
