    "body": "Just as a hint... I was thinking about something like this to also support the openshift uid security model....\r\n\r\n```\r\nFROM centos:latest\r\n\r\nENV VERSION=0.2.3\r\nENV HOME=\"/data\"\r\n\r\nCOPY bin/uid_entrypoint /usr/bin/uid_entrypoint\r\n\r\nRUN curl -L -o /usr/bin/beacon-chain https://github.com/prysmaticlabs/prysm/releases/download/v$VERSION/beacon-chain-v$VERSION-linux-amd64 && \\\r\n    curl -L -o /usr/bin/validator https://github.com/prysmaticlabs/prysm/releases/download/v$VERSION/validator-v$VERSION-linux-amd64 && \\\r\n\tchmod 755 /usr/bin/beacon-chain && \\\r\n\tchmod 755 /usr/bin/validator \\\r\n    chmod 755 /usr/bin/uid_entrypoint \\\r\n    mkdir /data && chmod 777 /data \\\r\n    chmod g=u /etc/passwd\r\n\r\nVOLUME /data\r\n\r\nWORKDIR /data\r\n\r\nEXPOSE 4000/tcp\r\nEXPOSE 7000/tcp\r\n\r\nCMD /usr/bin/beacon-chain \\\r\n    --bootstrap-node= \\\r\n    --deposit-contract=0xD775140349E6A5D12524C6ccc3d6A1d4519D4029 \\\r\n\t--p2p-port=4000 \\\r\n\t--grpc-gateway-port=7000 \\\r\n    --interop-genesis-state=\"\" \\\r\n\t--p2p-priv-key=/tmp/id.key \\\r\n    --datadir=/data \\\r\n\t--scatter\r\n\r\nENTRYPOINT [ \"/usr/bin/uid_entrypoint\" ]\r\n\r\nUSER 1001\r\n```\r\n```\r\n#!/bin/bash\r\n\r\nif ! whoami &> /dev/null; then\r\n  if [ -w /etc/passwd ]; then\r\n    echo \"${USER_NAME:-default}:x:$(id -u):0:${USER_NAME:-default} user:${HOME}:/sbin/nologin\" >> /etc/passwd\r\n  fi\r\nfi\r\n\r\nexec $@\r\n```\r\n",
