    "body": "I would probably recommend a builder pattern from a docker image since these are optimized for docker already. Take a look at how DappNode builds their docker images for beacon chain: https://github.com/eduadiez/DAppNodePackage-prysm-beacon-chain/blob/master/build/Dockerfile\r\n\r\n```dockerfile\r\nFROM gcr.io/prysmaticlabs/prysm/beacon-chain@sha256:113a07ab26a0e269cd0aee872f24464f163db353d658e32cc990e15fe205c856 as binary\r\n\r\nFROM alpine\r\n\r\n# Install dependencies\r\nRUN apk --update add bash ca-certificates libc6-compat && \\\r\n    rm  -rf /tmp/* /var/cache/apk/*\r\n\r\nCOPY --from=binary /app/beacon-chain/image.binary /usr/local/bin/beacon-chain\r\n\r\nENTRYPOINT beacon-chain --datadir=/data --init-sync-no-verify $EXTRA_OPTS\r\n```\r\n\r\nWith this, you can build upon or extend these docker images. However, we won't support anything other than the minimal docker images at this time. ",
