    "body": "Our docker images are essentially the go binary built for the architecture in a minimal image.\r\n\r\nThe base image we use is gcr.io/distroless/cc. See: https://github.com/GoogleContainerTools/distroless. Then we insert the built go binary. The only static bindings would be libc++, as far as I know. \r\n\r\nI think I understand your concern and we see an example of how to do this in the rules_docker repository readme: https://github.com/bazelbuild/rules_docker#go_image-custom-base I'll give this a try and report back here, thanks",
